subject: Baseball
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Sept. 21 (AP) — Philadelphia’s 48th come-from-behind victory was much easier on the nerves than many of the other 47. Home runs from Ryan Howard and Pat Burrell had the Phillies back in front before the third inning was done.
